add("Virtual List for Large Data", "ui", "Implement a virtual/windowed list for rendering 10,000+ items in [framework]:\n- Only render visible items + buffer\n- Fixed or variable row heights\n- Smooth scrolling without jank\n- Correct scrollbar behavior\n- Support for dynamic item heights\n- Use [react-window/react-virtualized/tanstack-virtual]\n- Maintain selection state while scrolling")
add("Responsive Card Grid", "ui", "Design a responsive card grid layout in [framework]:\n- CSS Grid with auto-fill and minmax\n- Card: image top, title, description, footer with tags\n- Image aspect ratio preserved (16:9)\n- Hover: slight lift with shadow\n- Equal height cards in each row\n- Skeleton loading variant\n- 3 columns desktop, 2 tablet, 1 mobile\n- Smooth layout transitions")
add("Stepper/Wizard Component", "ui", "Build a multi-step wizard/stepper in [framework]:\n- Step indicators showing progress\n- Completed steps: green check\n- Current step: active highlight\n- Future steps: gray/disabled\n- Next/Back/Submit buttons\n- Form validation before advancing\n- Step content with smooth slide transition\n- Save progress between steps\n- Responsive: vertical stepper on mobile")
add("Dropdown Select Component", "ui", "Create a custom dropdown select in [framework]:\n- Click to open options list\n- Search/filter within options\n- Keyboard navigation (arrows, enter, escape)\n- Multi-select variant with tags\n- Clear selection button\n- Loading state for async options\n- Group options with headers\n- Custom option rendering (icon + text)\n- Position: flip above if near bottom")
add("Tooltip Component", "ui", "Build a reusable tooltip component in [framework]:\n- Trigger on hover and focus\n- Positions: top, bottom, left, right (auto-flip)\n- Arrow pointing to trigger\n- Delay before show (200ms) and hide (100ms)\n- Rich content support (HTML)\n- Maximum width with word wrap\n- Dark background with light text\n- Accessible: role='tooltip' with aria-describedby\n- Dismiss on Escape key")
add("Accordion/Collapsible Component", "ui", "Create an accessible accordion in [framework]:\n- Click header to expand/collapse\n- Animated height transition (not display:none)\n- Only one section open at a time (optional)\n- Open/close icon rotation\n- Keyboard: Enter/Space to toggle, arrow keys between headers\n- ARIA: aria-expanded, aria-controls\n- Focus management after toggle\n- Nested accordion support")
add("Search Bar with Suggestions", "ui", "Build a search bar with autocomplete in [framework]:\n- Input with search icon\n- Dropdown suggestions on type (debounced 300ms)\n- Highlight matching text in suggestions\n- Keyboard: arrow keys to navigate, enter to select\n- Recent searches section\n- Category grouping in results\n- Loading spinner during fetch\n- Clear input X button\n- Click outside to dismiss")
add("Avatar Component with Fallback", "ui", "Create an avatar component in [framework]:\n- Image avatar with lazy loading\n- Fallback: user initials on colored background\n- Color generated from user name hash\n- Size variants: xs(24px), sm(32px), md(40px), lg(64px), xl(96px)\n- Status indicator dot (online, offline, busy)\n- Avatar group with overlap (+3 more)\n- Rounded and square variants\n- Loading skeleton state")
add("Notification Badge", "ui", "Build a notification badge component in [framework]:\n- Red dot for boolean indicator\n- Number badge for count\n- Max count display (99+)\n- Animate: pulse on new notification\n- Position: top-right of parent element\n- Size: auto-width based on content\n- Remove animation when clearing\n- Accessible: aria-label describing count")
add("Progress Bar Component", "ui", "Create a progress bar component in [framework]:\n- Linear and circular variants\n- Percentage label (inside or outside)\n- Color variants: default, success, warning, danger\n- Indeterminate mode (animated stripe)\n- Size variants: sm, md, lg\n- Animated fill on value change\n- Multi-segment variant (stacked)\n- Accessible: role='progressbar' with aria-valuenow")
add("Date Picker Component", "ui", "Build a date picker in [framework]:\n- Calendar grid with month/year navigation\n- Single date and date range selection\n- Min/max date constraints\n- Highlight today\n- Disable specific dates\n- Keyboard navigation (arrows, enter)\n- Mobile: native date input fallback\n- Format customization (MM/DD/YYYY, etc.)\n- Clear and today shortcut buttons")
add("Responsive Hero Section", "ui", "Design a hero section for a landing page in [framework]:\n- Full-width background (image, gradient, or video)\n- Large headline with subtext\n- CTA buttons (primary and secondary)\n- Scroll-down indicator\n- Responsive typography (fluid scaling)\n- Overlay for text readability\n- Animate elements on load (fade up, stagger)\n- Mobile: stacked layout, shorter text\n- Minimum viewport height")

# ===== API (50) =====
add("RESTful Resource Endpoints", "api", "Design and implement RESTful API endpoints for [resource] in [framework] with [database]:\n\nEndpoints:\n- GET /api/v1/[resource] - List with query params: page, limit, sort, filter\n- GET /api/v1/[resource]/:id - Get by ID with field selection\n- POST /api/v1/[resource] - Create with validation\n- PUT /api/v1/[resource]/:id - Full update\n- PATCH /api/v1/[resource]/:id - Partial update\n- DELETE /api/v1/[resource]/:id - Soft delete\n\nInclude: input validation, error handling, pagination metadata, consistent response format.")
add("GraphQL Schema Design", "api", "Design a GraphQL schema for [domain] with [entities]:\n\nCreate:\n1. Type definitions for each entity\n2. Query type: list (with pagination), getById, search\n3. Mutation type: create, update, delete\n4. Input types for mutations\n5. Custom scalar types (DateTime, JSON)\n6. Interface for common fields\n7. Connection types for cursor pagination\n8. Subscription for real-time updates")
add("GraphQL Resolvers", "api", "Implement GraphQL resolvers for this schema in [framework]:\n\n[schema]\n\nInclude:\n- Query resolvers with DataLoader for N+1 prevention\n- Mutation resolvers with input validation\n- Field resolvers for computed fields\n- Error handling with custom error codes\n- Authentication check in context\n- Permission guards per field")
add("JWT Authentication API", "api", "Implement JWT authentication endpoints in [framework]:\n\n- POST /api/auth/register - Create account\n- POST /api/auth/login - Returns access + refresh tokens\n- POST /api/auth/refresh - Exchange refresh for new access token\n- POST /api/auth/logout - Invalidate refresh token\n- GET /api/auth/me - Get current user\n\nSecurity:\n- Access token: 15min expiry, in Authorization header\n- Refresh token: 7 day expiry, httpOnly cookie\n- Password hashing with bcrypt (12 rounds)\n- Token blacklist on logout")
add("OAuth2 Authorization Server", "api", "Implement OAuth2 authorization endpoints in [framework]:\n\n- GET /oauth/authorize - Authorization endpoint\n- POST /oauth/token - Token endpoint\n- POST /oauth/revoke - Token revocation\n- GET /oauth/userinfo - User info endpoint\n\nSupport grant types:\n- Authorization code with PKCE\n- Refresh token\n- Client credentials\n\nInclude proper error responses per OAuth2 spec (RFC 6749).")
add("API Key Authentication", "api", "Implement API key authentication in [framework]:\n\n- Generate API keys: POST /api/keys\n- List keys: GET /api/keys\n- Revoke key: DELETE /api/keys/:id\n\nMiddleware:\n- Check X-API-Key header\n- Lookup key in database with caching\n- Rate limit per key\n- Track usage per key\n- Scope-based permissions per key\n- Hash stored keys (never store plain text)")
add("Rate Limiting Middleware", "api", "Implement rate limiting middleware in [framework]:\n\nAlgorithm: Sliding window with Redis\n\nLimits:\n- Anonymous: 30 requests/minute\n- Authenticated: 100 requests/minute\n- Admin: 500 requests/minute\n\nResponse headers:\n- X-RateLimit-Limit\n- X-RateLimit-Remaining\n- X-RateLimit-Reset\n\n429 response with Retry-After header on limit exceeded.\nDistributed support for multiple server instances.")
add("Request Validation Middleware", "api", "Create request validation middleware using [Joi/Zod/express-validator] in [framework]:\n\nValidation for:\n- Body: JSON schema validation\n- Query params: type coercion and bounds\n- URL params: format validation (UUID, slug)\n- Headers: required headers check\n\nFeatures:\n- Descriptive error messages per field\n- Sanitize input (trim, escape HTML)\n- Strip unknown fields\n- Consistent 400 error response format")
add("API Error Handling", "api", "Implement centralized API error handling in [framework]:\n\nCustom error classes:\n- ValidationError (400)\n- AuthenticationError (401)\n- ForbiddenError (403)\n- NotFoundError (404)\n- ConflictError (409)\n- RateLimitError (429)\n- InternalError (500)\n\nError response format:\n{ error: { code, message, details, requestId } }\n\nGlobal error handler middleware that logs and formats all errors consistently.")
add("API Versioning", "api", "Implement API versioning in [framework]:\n\nStrategy: URL path versioning (/api/v1, /api/v2)\n\nSetup:\n1. Version-specific route registration\n2. Shared middleware across versions\n3. Version-specific controllers\n4. Deprecation headers for old versions\n5. Version sunset schedule\n6. Documentation per version\n7. Request routing based on version")
add("Cursor-Based Pagination API", "api", "Implement cursor-based pagination for [entity] API in [framework]:\n\nEndpoint: GET /api/[entity]?cursor=abc&limit=20&direction=next\n\nResponse:\n{\n  data: [...],\n  pagination: {\n    hasNextPage: true,\n    hasPreviousPage: false,\n    startCursor: 'abc',\n    endCursor: 'xyz',\n    totalCount: 1500\n  }\n}\n\nUse indexed column for cursor (created_at + id for uniqueness).\nSupport forward and backward pagination.")
add("File Upload API", "api", "Implement file upload endpoints in [framework]:\n\n- POST /api/upload - Single file upload (multipart)\n- POST /api/upload/multiple - Multiple files\n- POST /api/upload/presigned - Get presigned URL for direct-to-S3\n- GET /api/files/:id - Get file metadata\n- DELETE /api/files/:id - Delete file\n\nFeatures:\n- File type whitelist validation\n- Max file size enforcement\n- Virus scanning integration point\n- Thumbnail generation for images\n- Unique filename generation\n- Store in [S3/local/CloudStorage]")
add("WebSocket Server", "api", "Implement a WebSocket server in [framework]:\n\nSetup:\n1. WebSocket upgrade handling\n2. Authentication on connection (JWT in query/header)\n3. Room/channel management (join, leave)\n4. Message broadcasting to room members\n5. Heartbeat ping/pong (30s interval)\n6. Graceful disconnection handling\n7. Reconnection support\n8. Message acknowledgment system\n9. Rate limiting per connection")
add("Authentication Middleware", "api", "Create authentication middleware for [framework]:\n\nFeatures:\n1. Extract token from Authorization header or cookie\n2. Verify JWT signature and expiration\n3. Attach user object to request\n4. Handle expired tokens (401 with specific code)\n5. Handle invalid tokens (401)\n6. Optional auth (some routes need user if available)\n7. Role-based route protection\n8. Refresh token rotation on near-expiry")
add("Database Connection Pool", "api", "Configure database connection pooling in [framework] with [database]:\n\nSettings:\n- Pool size: min 5, max 20\n- Connection timeout: 10 seconds\n- Idle timeout: 30 seconds\n- Max lifetime: 1 hour\n\nImplement:\n1. Pool initialization on app start\n2. Health check query on checkout\n3. Connection retry on failure\n4. Graceful shutdown (drain pool)\n5. Pool metrics logging\n6. Separate read/write pools for replicas")
add("ORM Model Definitions", "api", "Define [ORM] models for the following entities in [framework]:\n\n[entity descriptions with fields]\n\nFor each model:\n1. Column definitions with types and constraints\n2. Relationships (hasMany, belongsTo, manyToMany)\n3. Timestamps (createdAt, updatedAt)\n4. Soft delete support\n5. Indexes for query optimization\n6. Validation rules\n7. Scopes for common queries\n8. Serialization (toJSON with field exclusion)")
add("Database Migration", "api", "Create database migrations for [schema changes] in [framework]:\n\nChanges:\n[describe schema changes]\n\nMigration must:\n1. Be reversible (up and down)\n2. Handle existing data\n3. Be safe for zero-downtime deployment\n4. Add indexes after data migration\n5. Use transactions where supported\n6. Include data transformation if needed\n7. Test with production-like data volume")
add("Redis Cache Implementation", "api", "Implement Redis caching layer for [framework] API:\n\nCache strategies:\n1. Cache-aside for GET endpoints\n2. Write-through for POST/PUT\n3. TTL: 5min for lists, 15min for single items\n4. Cache key format: 'entity:id' and 'entity:list:hash(params)'\n5. Cache invalidation on mutations\n6. Cache warming for popular items\n7. Redis connection pooling\n8. Fallback to database on cache miss/failure")
add("Message Queue Integration", "api", "Integrate [RabbitMQ/SQS/Redis] message queue in [framework]:\n\nSetup:\n1. Producer: publish events from API handlers\n2. Consumer: process messages with worker\n3. Dead letter queue for failed messages\n4. Retry logic (3 attempts, exponential backoff)\n5. Message acknowledgment\n6. Queue monitoring and metrics\n7. Graceful shutdown (finish current message)\n\nEvents: [list event types like user.created, order.placed]")
add("Webhook Delivery System", "api", "Build a webhook delivery system in [framework]:\n\n- POST /api/webhooks - Register endpoint\n- GET /api/webhooks - List registrations\n- DELETE /api/webhooks/:id - Remove\n- POST /api/webhooks/:id/test - Send test event\n\nDelivery:\n1. HMAC-SHA256 signature in header\n2. Async delivery via job queue\n3. Retry: 3 attempts at 1min, 5min, 30min\n4. Log all delivery attempts with response\n5. Disable after 10 consecutive failures\n6. Webhook secret rotation support")
add("OpenAPI/Swagger Documentation", "api", "Generate OpenAPI 3.0 documentation for [framework] API:\n\n1. Define all endpoints with:\n   - HTTP method, path, description\n   - Request body schemas\n   - Query/path parameter definitions\n   - Response schemas for all status codes\n   - Authentication requirements\n2. Reusable component schemas\n3. Example requests and responses\n4. Server URLs for each environment\n5. Serve Swagger UI at /api/docs")
add("CORS Configuration", "api", "Configure CORS for [framework] API:\n\nSettings:\n- Allowed origins: [list of frontend URLs]\n- Allowed methods: GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE, OPTIONS\n- Allowed headers: Content-Type, Authorization, X-Request-ID\n- Exposed headers: X-RateLimit-Remaining, X-Request-ID\n- Credentials: true (for cookies)\n- Max age: 86400 (24h preflight cache)\n- Handle OPTIONS preflight requests\n- Reject requests from unauthorized origins")
add("Health Check Endpoint", "api", "Implement health check endpoints in [framework]:\n\n- GET /health/live - Liveness (app is running)\n- GET /health/ready - Readiness (dependencies OK)\n\nReadiness checks:\n1. Database connection with timeout (5s)\n2. Redis connection\n3. External API availability\n4. Disk space > 10%\n5. Memory usage < 90%\n\nResponse: { status: 'healthy'|'degraded'|'unhealthy', checks: {...}, uptime, version }")
add("Background Job Processor", "api", "Implement background job processing in [framework]:\n\nSetup with [Bull/Agenda/Celery]:\n1. Job queue with named queues (email, report, cleanup)\n2. Job scheduling (immediate, delayed, recurring)\n3. Job priority levels\n4. Concurrency control per queue\n5. Job progress tracking\n6. Failed job retry with backoff\n7. Job completion/failure events\n8. Admin dashboard for job monitoring\n9. Graceful shutdown (complete running jobs)")
add("Email Sending Service", "api", "Create an email service in [framework]:\n\n- POST /api/email/send - Send single email\n- POST /api/email/bulk - Send batch emails\n- GET /api/email/templates - List templates\n\nFeatures:\n1. Template engine ([Handlebars/EJS]) for HTML emails\n2. SMTP configuration ([SendGrid/SES/Mailgun])\n3. Queue emails for async sending\n4. Track delivery status\n5. Rate limiting (max 100/hour)\n6. Unsubscribe handling\n7. Attachment support\n8. Plain text fallback generation")
add("Search API with Elasticsearch", "api", "Implement search API using Elasticsearch in [framework]:\n\n- GET /api/search?q=term&type=entity&page=1\n\nFeatures:\n1. Index management (create, update, delete)\n2. Document indexing on CRUD operations\n3. Full-text search with relevance scoring\n4. Autocomplete/suggest endpoint\n5. Faceted search (filter by category, date, etc.)\n6. Highlight matched terms\n7. Fuzzy matching for typos\n8. Aggregation for analytics\n9. Index aliasing for zero-downtime reindex")
add("Batch Processing API", "api", "Implement batch processing endpoints in [framework]:\n\n- POST /api/batch - Submit batch operation\n- GET /api/batch/:id - Get batch status\n- DELETE /api/batch/:id - Cancel batch\n\nFeatures:\n1. Accept array of operations (max 100)\n2. Process async with progress tracking\n3. Per-item success/failure reporting\n4. Partial failure handling (continue on error)\n5. Rate limiting for batch submissions\n6. Result download when complete\n7. Batch expiration (cleanup after 24h)")
add("Server-Sent Events API", "api", "Implement Server-Sent Events (SSE) in [framework]:\n\n- GET /api/events/stream - SSE endpoint\n\nFeatures:\n1. Event stream with proper headers (text/event-stream)\n2. Named events (update, notification, heartbeat)\n3. Client authentication via query token\n4. Heartbeat every 15 seconds\n5. Reconnection with Last-Event-ID\n6. Event history replay on reconnect\n7. Connection limit per user\n8. Graceful connection cleanup")
add("API Gateway Pattern", "api", "Implement an API gateway in [framework]:\n\nFeatures:\n1. Route requests to microservices\n2. Authentication at gateway level\n3. Rate limiting per client\n4. Request/response transformation\n5. Load balancing between service instances\n6. Circuit breaker for failing services\n7. Request logging and tracing\n8. API key management\n9. Response caching\n10. Aggregate responses from multiple services")
add("Pagination with Total Count", "api", "Implement offset-based pagination with total count in [framework]:\n\nGET /api/[entity]?page=1&limit=20&sort=createdAt&order=desc\n\nResponse:\n{\n  data: [...],\n  meta: {\n    page: 1,\n    limit: 20,\n    totalItems: 523,\n    totalPages: 27,\n    hasNextPage: true,\n    hasPreviousPage: false\n  }\n}\n\nOptimize: use COUNT estimate for large tables, exact count for filtered queries.")
add("Soft Delete Implementation", "api", "Implement soft delete pattern for [entity] in [framework] with [ORM]:\n\n1. Add deletedAt column (nullable timestamp)\n2. Override delete to set deletedAt\n3. Default scope excludes soft-deleted records\n4. withDeleted scope to include all\n5. Restore endpoint: POST /api/[entity]/:id/restore\n6. Permanent delete after 30 days (scheduled job)\n7. Cascade soft delete to related records\n8. Unique constraints with soft delete consideration")
add("Multi-Tenant API", "api", "Implement multi-tenant API in [framework]:\n\nTenant resolution:\n1. From subdomain (tenant.app.com)\n2. From header (X-Tenant-ID)\n3. From JWT claim\n\nData isolation:\n- Shared database with tenant_id column\n- Middleware sets tenant context\n- All queries automatically filtered by tenant\n- Cross-tenant access prevention\n- Tenant-specific configuration\n- Admin endpoints for tenant management")
add("Audit Trail API", "api", "Implement audit trail endpoints in [framework]:\n\n- GET /api/audit-logs - List with filters\n- GET /api/audit-logs/:entityType/:entityId - Entity history\n\nLogging middleware:\n1. Capture before/after state on mutations\n2. Record: userId, action, entityType, entityId, changes, ip, timestamp\n3. Store in separate audit table\n4. Immutable (no update/delete on audit records)\n5. Query by user, entity, action, date range\n6. Export as CSV")
add("Idempotent API Design", "api", "Make these API endpoints idempotent in [framework]:\n\n[list of endpoints]\n\nImplementation:\n1. Accept Idempotency-Key header for POST requests\n2. Store request hash with response for 24 hours\n3. Return cached response for duplicate requests\n4. Use Redis for idempotency key storage\n5. Handle concurrent duplicate requests\n6. Return 409 if key reused with different payload")
add("API Response Compression", "api", "Implement response compression in [framework]:\n\n1. Enable gzip and Brotli compression\n2. Compress responses > 1KB\n3. Content-Type whitelist (JSON, HTML, CSS, JS)\n4. Accept-Encoding header negotiation\n5. Vary header for caching correctness\n6. Skip compression for already compressed (images)\n7. Benchmark: measure response size reduction\n8. Configure compression level (balance speed vs size)")

